          "date": "2016-04-25 06:00:08.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bhagyesh Dudhediya",
          "email": "bhagyesh.dudhediya@seagate.com",
          "date": "2016-04-25 06:38:21.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-8062 test: fix fail_val in recovery-small/115b",
        "message": "LU-8062 test: fix fail_val in recovery-small/115b\n\nThe fail_loc OBD_FAIL_OST_ENOSPC is caught in 2 places:\n1. ofd_statfs() - where it is checked against the fail_val\nand if fail_val matches the OST ID it is caught here\nitself and hence test fails.\n2. tgt_brw_write() - the actual place where the fail_loc should\nbe caught.\n\nThe patch makes the fail_loc to be caught at the appropriate place\nby setting the fail_val to $OSTCOUNT. So even if fail_loc is set\nin the statfs part it is not caught there and therefore caught in\ntgt_brw_write().\n\nSeagate-bug-id: MRP-3150\nChange-Id: I88cb713bd8de52de79937d338fb2533d99c1ee0f\nSigned-off-by: Bhagyesh Dudhediya <bhagyesh.dudhediya@seagate.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
